The paper deals with a data structure to answer reverse nearest neighbor queries in fixed-dimensional Euclidean space. This problem is relevant in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) where reverse nearest neighbor queries are used. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the data structure in databases (cs.DB) for efficient query processing.
